title: For Sale:  What a mess!
postcontent: I come to this site as an avid gun collector/shooter. I don't sell very often. Mostly, i buy things I haven't tried yet. Occasionally though, I will list something that didn't suit me personally, or something I was under-impressed with. At best, I might break even. Usually, I'll leave money on the table. Rarely have I considered myself to have made a profit! For the most part, I have met, and dealt with some mighty fine individuals! Most of you are decent, forthright people. There are, exceptions to everything though, and I have noticed more and more, a pattern of rudeness, and outright insulting replies to things I have listed. Or, those who refuse to make a phone call, but will text while driving to meet you! Let's not forget those that set up a meeting, then don't show up at all!Not sure if it's just the millennial crowd, who think we "OWE" them a firearm for a fraction of what it cost new? Or, the proliferation of those looking to make a quick "buck" by sending ridiculous low offers, and testing the waters.To those of you who actually love firearms, shooting, and meeting new people to buy, sell, and trade.... My apologies for taking up the time it took you to read this! To the others.... "Guess which finger I'm holding up!"
